OL,3,CMartyn's Law receives Royal Assent
OL,4,Cafter campaign by Martyn Hett's mother
OL,6,FThese businesses will be asked to
OL,7,Fundertake simple yet effective
OL,8,Factivities to put in place procedures
OL,9,Fto reduce harm to the public in the
OL,10,Fevent of an attack. These could be as
OL,11,Fsimple as training staff to lock
OL,12,Fdoors, close shutters and identify a
OL,13,Fsafe route to cover.
OL,15,FThe enhanced tier will apply to
OL,16,Fpremises and events with a capacity of
OL,17,Fmore than 800 individuals, given the
OL,18,Fdevastating impact an attack could
OL,19,Fhave in these spaces. These locations
OL,20,Fwill need to put in place measures
OL,21,Fsuch as CCTV or hiring security staff.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/16
